parameters:
After hitting me, Suzuki was suspended for a month, but
during that time, it seems he went through a lot of trouble,
like his father's company suddenly going bankrupt and his
father himself getting arrested.

According to the news, Suzuki's father was habitually using
dangerous drugs, forcing employees to work illegally in his
company, and engaging in backdoor deals, among other
criminal activities.

With his father's arrest, the Suzuki family fell apart, and
Suzuki, left behind alone, couldn't even attend school
anymore. Now, he's desperately scraping by with day labor
jobs.

He seems to have lived without any inconveniences until now,
so he must be struggling a lot. It's what you'd call poetic
justice, but I can't help feeling a bit sorry for him.

Regardless, peace has returned to the academy once again.
Since then, we've been enjoying our days without any issues.
Today, too, I was enjoying lunch break on the rooftop with
Makoto.
